Add support partial name match and job position to Find command
commitResults.messageBody:
Find command only supports full-word matching of names.
It also lacks the ability to filter by job position.

This makes it difficult for users to perform flexible searches.
For example, searching for "jack" will not return "Jackson".
Also, users cannot narrow down persons based on their job roles.

Let's,
* switch name matching from full-word to substring-based
* introduce the 'jp/' prefix to allow job position filtering
* combine both filters under the same Find command
* extend the FindCommandParser to support multiple prefixes
* update predicate logic to allow OR combination of conditions

Using substring matching makes the search experience more forgiving and
user-friendly. Supporting job position search through a dedicated prefix
also improves the expressiveness and precision of the Find command.

This approach keeps FindCommand simple and extensible, and aligns with how
other commands (e.g., add, edit) use prefixes for clarity.
